(? Header row contains:) Tj
T*
(? timestamp) Tj
T*
(? project name) Tj
T*
(? project code) Tj
T*
(? reporting period text) Tj
T*
(? many paired metric columns \(plan/actual\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(WHAT IMPORTER DOES) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. Reads sheet 1 and detects core columns.) Tj
T*
(2. Detects metric columns by plan/actual keywords.) Tj
T*
(3. Normalizes project codes and period ranges.) Tj
T*
(4. Creates missing me_projects and me_reporting_periods \(when table exists\).) Tj
T*
(5. Auto-creates missing me_indicators for detected metrics.) Tj
T*
(6. Upserts:) Tj
T*
(? plan values -> me_indicator_targets) Tj
T*
(? actual values -> me_indicator_reports \(source=import\)) Tj
T*
(7. Writes debug JSON report to:) Tj
T*
(? storage/app/me-import-reports/weekly-import-YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS.json) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(IDEMPOTENCY) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(? Re-importing same file updates existing records \(upsert\) rather than duplicating rows.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(7\) OBSERVER BEHAVIOR) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Observer: App\\Observers\\ME\\MeIndicatorReportObserver) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(? On report save, it attempts to synchronize alerts through AlertService.) Tj
T*
(? It safely skips/ignores sync when alert tables are unavailable during setup/import bootstrap.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(8\) NOTES FOR FUTURE CHANGES) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(? If headers are renamed later \(for example fully English\), importer still works as long as:) Tj
T*
(? project name/code and period columns are present) Tj
T*
(? metric columns still include recognizable plan/actual semantics) Tj
T*
(? For strict template enforcement, implement a dedicated header map and validation mode.) Tj
ET
